<title type="html"><![CDATA[9/26(Thu) Self-hypnosis/Your body language may shape who you are (Host: Linda Fun)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=319&amp;p=335#p335"><![CDATA[
Session One: Self-hypnosis<br /><br />Please click the following link to read the article.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.healthline.com/health/is-hypnosis-real">https://www.healthline.com/health/is-hypnosis-real</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q1. Do you think hypnosis is real or fake? Why? How about meditation and mindfulness? Have you tried any of them?<br />Q2.Many athletes use hypnosis to improve performance, and release anxiety. Do you think it’s more effective than the placebo?<br />Q3. “Beauty is in the eye of the beholder.” People are easily hypnotized by their lovers and become better.<br />   Do you think self-hypnosis is a good tool to improve yourself?<br />Q4. Hypnosis is not “mind-controlled”, no one can be hypnotized against their will. If it’s safe and effective, are you willing to try it?<br /> <br /><br />Session Two: Your body language may shape who you are<br /><br />Please click the following link to watch the video.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ks-_Mh1QhMc&amp;t=686s">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ks-_Mh1QhMc&amp;t=686s</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q5. Do you think your body language may change your mind, and feelings?  Can you share your experiences?<br />Q6. According to the video, we smile when we are happy, and we are happy when we smile. Do you think <br />“笑笑功” could be an effective way to help us feel happy? <br />Q7. Can power posing for a few minutes really change your life in meaningful ways? If so, are you willing to <br />try high power poses to build your confidence when having job interview or standing on stage?<br /><br />***************************************************************************************<br />Suggested Agenda<br />7:00 p.m. --7:30 p.m. Free talk<br />7:30 p.m. --8:10 p.m. First topic discussion<br />8:10 p.m. --8:40 p.m. Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:40 p.m.-- 9.:15 p.m. Second topic discussion<br />9:15 p.m.-- 9:30 p.m. Presentation (Participants that haven't presented yet are invited)<br /><br />speaker time: 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time: 3 minutes<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第三區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=13721">morris</a> — Fri Sep 20, 2019 10:54 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
